Are you a Back-End Web Developer with eCommerce experience?  My client is looking for someone to join their team of developers to maintain and carry out new web development projects.  They have a great location in the North Galleria and offer fantastic benefits.  Looking to interview immediately!   
 Responsibilities:   
Configure and maintain Magento and WordPress to work with other business tools; 
Implement/consume REST services; 
Maintain PCI compliance requirements; 
Provide suggestions and recommendations for new technology solutions; 
Monitor scheduled database and application backups; 
Adhere to code standards; 
Maintain the web infrastructure for high availability of critical e-commerce operations. 
Perform continuous web site improvements and optimizations; 
Review, evaluate, analyze and modify existing programming as necessary; 
Work collaboratively with other teams on projects to improve and enhance our websites. 

  Requirements:   
Bachelor's degree or higher in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Information Systems or another related field; 
Minimum 2 years of back-end web development experience; 
Knowledge of e-commerce and database operations; 
Comfortable in a Linux/Apache/MySQL/PHP (LAMP) environment; 
Strong knowledge of web frameworks; 
Strong technical knowledge of the following: XML, PHP, SQL, JavaScript, jQuery, AJAX, MySQL, Prototype, HTML5, CSS3; 
Strong PHP, OOP, and MVC principles and design patterns; 
Ability to work in a fast-paced, task-focused, team environment; 
Strong initiative and self-starting approach; 
Ability to operate effectively during rapid growth; 
Great attention to details; 
Excellent problem-solving skills; 
Experience working with responsive and mobile web development; 
Ability to work effectively in a fast-paced environment with low tolerance for error. 

  Bonus:   
Knowledge of or experience in natural health industry; 
Actively embraces healthy living; 
Believes in helping others; 
Enjoys making a positive change in the world; 
Knowledge of SEO best practices; 
Available after-hours for servers/application troubleshooting; 
RedHat/CentOS, AWS, AMP

			Minimum Required Skills:
Back-End Development, NodeJS, ExpressJS, RESTful APIs, NoSQL, Relational Databases

If you are a Back End Software Engineer with experience, please read on!

What You Will Be Doing

The Back End engineer is responsible for building clean, optimized, maintainable and extensible APIs.

Responsibilities:
Working closely with mobile engineers and other system engineers to architect backend system and build clean, optimized APIs;
Developing and maintaining the highest performance and uptime system;
Writing both unit and integration tests;
Participating in peer code review process to keep code quality high;
Collaborating with other API engineers and backend team members to improve the quality of our APIs and assist in establishing best practices / processes across our products

What You Need for this Position

Required:
Expert with Nodejs, Express;
Proficient with designing RESTful APIs;
In-depth understanding of software engineering principles and practices;
Experience with scaling system architecture and identifying common performance bottlenecks;
Excellent troubleshooting and debugging skills;
Experience with statically typed languages is desirable;
Expertise at resolving real world issues within API development;
Track record of providing clean, concise documentation to other developers, is desired;
Has been through Software Development Life Cycle;

Plus:
Experience with relational database and/or NoSQL database -- a big plus;
Experience with web front end development -- a plus;
Comfortable in working in startup culture and environment;
Interest in growing and participating in development best practices;
Interest in pushing development boundaries with new technologies is a nice to have;

Experience:
MS degree in Computer Science with 3+ years of backend development experience;
Or BS degree in Computer Science with very strong backend development experience would be considered;

